From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 17:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 25/25] Remove empty per-project Plans dir at session end
 (rmdir-only)

Upstream issue: (pai-nix — hygiene; no upstream issue.)

The release settings.json ships `"plansDirectory": "Plans/"` — a
RELATIVE path in a GLOBAL settings file. claude-code resolves it
against each session's project root and creates the directory
eagerly in its memoized path-resolver (`mkdirSync` on first resolve,
verified in claude-code 2.1.170), even when plan mode is never used.
Net result on a real machine: 64 `Plans/` directories across every
project ever opened, 49 of them empty litter, 15 with real plans.

Upstream offers no lazy-creation option and no disable value, and
the eager mkdir lives inside the minified claude-code binary, where
patching it would break on every claude-code update. So instead of
preventing the creation, this patch makes SessionCleanup (already a
SessionEnd hook) remove the directory at session end IF AND ONLY IF
it is still empty:

  - stdin parse now also captures `cwd` (standard hook input field;
    if absent, the cleanup is skipped entirely — fail-safe is "do
    nothing").
  - after clearSessionWork(), a single `rmdirSync(join(cwd, 'Plans'))`
    wrapped in try/catch.

SAFETY CONTRACT (the reason this is rmdir and nothing else):
rmdir(2) deletes ONLY an empty directory. Non-empty fails with
ENOTEMPTY, missing with ENOENT, a symlink with ENOTDIR — it cannot
recurse and does not follow links, so a project with real plan
files keeps them by construction, not by logic that could regress.
No rm, no rmSync, no recursive/force options anywhere. The catch
block swallows all three errno cases and changes nothing.

Known residual (accepted, rare): two concurrent sessions in the SAME
project — one ends (removes the still-empty dir), the other later
saves its first plan; whether that save re-creates the directory is
claude-code's concern. Window requires concurrent same-project
sessions AND first plan-mode use ordered after the other session's
end.

Behavioral effect: projects where plan mode is used keep their local
Plans/ exactly as before; projects where it is not used stop
accumulating empty directories (removed at each clean session end).
Pre-existing empty dirs from before this patch disappear the next
time a session in that project ends cleanly.

Files touched (paths relative to upstream source root):

  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/SessionCleanup.hook.ts  (docstring,
    fs import, stdin parse, post-clearSessionWork cleanup block)

Total: 1 file, 5 hunks.

Verification: substitutions applied against the hash-verified
upstream v5.0.0 source (nix store FOD); `git apply --check` clean;
functional matrix with synthetic SessionEnd stdin under isolated
HOME/PAI_DIR: empty Plans/ removed, Plans/ with a file untouched
(file intact), missing Plans/ exits 0, symlinked Plans/ untouched
with target intact; `bun build --no-bundle` parses the patched file.
Hunks generated via `diff -u` against the upstream v5.0.0 source
tree.
